         UI/UX design, interaction logic and visual elements; color
         schemes, typography and brand visual identity; artwork,
         illustrations, pixel art and digital paintings; articles,
         prose, poetry, commentary and all written works; creative
         concepts, design philosophy and documentation; audio,
         animation, video and multimedia content; data structures,
         database designs and content organization; configuration
         files and build tooling; the overall structure, directory
         organization and presentation of this repository itself;
         and any portion, fragment, screenshot or derivative form
         of any of the foregoing.

    1.3  "You" means any individual, group, company, institution,
         organization, automated system or AI agent that accesses,
         reads or interacts with this repository in any manner.

    1.4  "Third-Party Components" means any libraries, APIs,
         frameworks, fonts, tools or other materials created by
         parties other than the Author that may be referenced or
         used within this repository.

    1.5  "Authorization" means exclusively a prior, explicit,
         written permission granted by the Author in accordance
         with the procedure set out in Article 4. No other form
         of permission constitutes a valid Authorization under
         this License.


Article 2  Grant of Rights


    No rights are granted to You by default under this License.

    The only activity permitted without Authorization is viewing
    the Content online through its official channel. Such viewing
    does not constitute Authorization or permission of any kind.

    Any use of the Content beyond the above viewing requires prior
    written Authorization from the Author. See Article 4 for the
    request procedure.


Article 3  Restrictions


    Without Authorization, You may not, under any circumstance,
    for any purpose, via any medium, in any industry or jurisdiction,
    perform any of the following acts:


    Section 1  Reproduction and Storage

        (i)   Reproduce, download, cache, screenshot, screen-record,
              print or store all or any part of the Content by any
              means whatsoever;

        (ii)  Retrieve or scrape the Content in bulk via browser
              plugins, crawlers, scripts, mirroring tools or any
              other automated or technical means;

        (iii) Store the Content on any local device, server, cloud
              storage, network drive or offline medium.


    Section 2  Distribution and Dissemination

        (i)   Publish, repost, forward, distribute, broadcast or
              transmit the Content in any form;

        (ii)  Upload the Content to any platform, website, forum,
              database, cloud storage, social media or content
              delivery network;

        (iii) Transmit the Content to any third party via email,
              instant messaging, direct message or any other
              communication tool;

        (iv)  Indirectly disseminate the Content via mirroring,
              proxies or forwarding services;

        (v)   Describe or reconstruct the core structure or
              substantive content of the Content to others by
              any means, whether verbally, in writing or otherwise.


    Section 3  Modification and Derivative Works

        (i)   Modify, edit, crop, translate, adapt or rearrange
              the Content in any way;

        (ii)  Create any derivative work based on, referencing
              or inspired by the Content;

        (iii) Merge, mix or integrate the Content with other
              content for presentation or publication in any form;

        (iv)  Imitate the style, structure, layout or visual
              language of the Content and publish such imitation.


    Section 4  Commercial Use

        (i)   Use the Content for any commercial purpose, including
              but not limited to sales, advertising, promotion,
              fundraising, competitive bidding and commercial
              presentations;

        (ii)  File for any patent, trademark, copyright registration
              or other intellectual property right using the Content;

        (iii) Use the Content in any for-profit product, service
              or platform;

        (iv)  Use the Content as leverage or consideration in any
              commercial negotiation or collaboration.


    Section 5  Artificial Intelligence and Data Use

        (i)   Use the Content to train, fine-tune, test or evaluate
              any artificial intelligence, machine learning or deep
              learning model or algorithm;

        (ii)  Include the Content in any dataset, corpus, vector
              store or knowledge base;

        (iii) Use any AI tool to analyze, summarize, extract or
              structure the Content and publish the output;

        (iv)  Allow any automated system to read, index or process
              the Content for any purpose.


    Section 6  Academic and Educational Use

        (i)   Cite, reproduce or use the Content in any academic
              paper, research report, teaching material or course
              content;

        (ii)  Use the Content in any public lecture, academic
              presentation, professional training or educational
              setting.


    Section 7  Press and Media Use

        (i)   Cite, display or describe the Content in any news
              report, media interview, commentary article or
              self-media content;

        (ii)  Screenshot or record the Content and distribute
              such material publicly.


    Section 8  Attribution and Rights Claims

        (i)   Remove, obscure or alter any copyright notice,
              attribution, watermark or rights identifier contained
              in the Content;

        (ii)  Claim ownership, authorship or any usage rights over
              the Content in any manner;

        (iii) Publicly mention, display or associate the Content
              without Authorization.


    Section 9  Technical Circumvention

        (i)   Attempt to circumvent, crack or bypass any technical
              protection measure applied to the Content;

        (ii)  Reverse-engineer, decompile or disassemble the Content;

        (iii) Obtain any unpublished portion or source file of the
