    Section 10  Indirect Acts and Facilitation

        (i)   Assist, induce, permit, fund or condone any third party
              in committing any act prohibited under this Article;

        (ii)  Provide tools, platforms or other means that enable
              any third party to commit any act prohibited under
              this Article.


Article 4  Authorization Procedure


    To request Authorization, the applicant must satisfy all of
    the following conditions simultaneously. The absence of any
    single condition renders the Authorization invalid:

        (a)  Submit a formal written application to the Author via
             GitHub Issues, clearly stating the intended purpose,
             scope, duration and method of use;

        (b)  Receive explicit written confirmation of Authorization
             from the Author;

        (c)  Execute the written authorization agreement provided
             by the Author;

        (d)  Comply strictly with all terms and conditions set out
             in the authorization agreement throughout its duration;

        (e)  Immediately cease all use and delete all related Content
             upon expiration of the Authorization.

    The following do not constitute valid Authorization under this
    License: verbal agreements or verbal permissions; implied
    licenses or permissions inferred from conduct; unilateral
    declarations or interpretations by either party; permissions
    conveyed or relayed through third parties; and expired or
    out-of-scope historical authorizations.

    Contact: https://github.com/ERX399


